§ Why ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ If we scale an integrable function is the resulting function
    integrable? ⦉

  ‖ If so, what is its integral? ⦉
⦉

§ Result ⦉
<statement type='proposition'>
  ‖ Suppose $f: 𝗥 → 𝗥$ is integrable. ⦉

  ‖ Then for any $λ ∈ 𝗥$, the function $λf$ is integrable and
    ◇ ⦊
      ‖ ∫λf = λ∫f ⦉
    ⦉⦉
</statement>
